# SiteLink backend — env var reference (copy to backend/.env and fill in).
#
# NEVER commit a real backend/.env. This *.example lists the OPTIONAL, KEY-GATED
# integration secrets. Required core vars (DATABASE_URL, SUPABASE_*, JWT secret)
# live in per-environment secret stores (Architecture §8), never in the repo —
# see .env.local.example for the local-dev throwaway set.

# ── Reports: CloudConvert (HTML→PDF) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL. When set, /reports/*.pdf render via CloudConvert; when UNSET the back
# end falls back to the in-process @react-pdf renderer. Secret — never commit.
# CLOUDCONVERT_API_KEY="your-cloudconvert-api-key-here"

# ── Payslip share: EMAIL via SMTP (nodemailer) ───────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL + KEY-GATED. The "email payslip PDF to worker" feature is DISABLED
# until ALL of SMTP_HOST + SMTP_USER + SMTP_PASS + EMAIL_FROM are set; until then
# POST /reports/payslip/email returns 503 'Email sending is not configured'
# (it never attempts a send). Universal: point at any SMTP provider (Gmail
# app-password, SendGrid, Mailgun, SES, Postmark, …). SMTP_USER + SMTP_PASS are
# SECRET and never logged/echoed. SMTP_PORT defaults to 587 (STARTTLS); use 465
# for implicit TLS.
# SMTP_HOST="smtp.your-provider.com"
# SMTP_PORT="587"
# SMTP_USER="your-smtp-username"
# SMTP_PASS="your-smtp-password-or-app-key"
# EMAIL_FROM="SiteLink <no-reply@yourco.com>"
